Defendant Derrick E Hall in court with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.  Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea Colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

150 days  Huber (Credit - 0 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.

Term of Probation: 12 Months

Conditions of Probation:
- No Use or Possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Obtain a valid license within first 6 months of probation;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Costs: $268.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00
(To be paid within the first 6 months of probation at the rate of $100.00  per month commencing 1-15-15. Failure to pay  the Court orders 4 days Huber as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
